            "answer_text": "There is no future at all when math ceases to exist. Right at the moment when math disappears, it means there is no physics, no chemistry, no biology, no humans, no life. There is absolutely nothing. Even Emptiness called zero-point energy by physicists will not exist despite the fact that we do not know laws governing it yet. Because, when there will be some laws of it discovered, again, they will be mathematically founded ones like all other laws governing different layers of reality that we already know and study. Simply said, mathematics was so far found in all what we observe, and partially is even observed in what we do not understand, cannot observe directly, and is beyond our comprehension at this time and place. We always succeeded to find some rules called mathematics behind and inside of all what is observed in the Nature. ",
